# HABITAT Skills Assessment & Website Build Plan

## Current State Analysis

### 🎯 What You Have
Your **habitat-skills** repo is a solid foundation with **11 skills across 4 phases**:

| Phase | Skills | Purpose |
|-------|--------|---------|
| **Ideation & Validation** | founder-context, idea-validation, competitor-research, customer-segments | Help founders define and validate their startup idea |
| **Prototyping & Building** | landing-page, prototype-sprint, mvp-scope | Guide the build process |
| **Demo & Pitch** | pitch-deck | Prepare for presenting |
| **Launch & Traction** | first-users, launch-plan, social-content | Post-launch growth guidance |

### 📊 Gap Assessment

#### What's Missing from habitat-skills:
1. **No showcase website** - The repo works but there's no front-facing site to explain the value proposition and drive adoption
2. **No interactive demo** - People can't try the skills without installing Claude Code first
3. **Limited documentation** - Skills exist but no guided journey or tutorials
4. **No community/testimonials** - Missing social proof from 101+ founders who used Habitat

#### Opportunity:
Build a **stunning website** that:
- Showcases the habitat-skills framework
- Drives signups for Habitat events
- Potentially hosts an interactive version of the Sprint app

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Scope Decision Needed**: There are two possible project scopes:
>
> **Option A: Marketing Website Only** (~3-4 hours)
> - Beautiful landing page for Habitat ecosystem
> - Showcase skills, events, testimonials
> - Inspired by Creators Corner, SPC, ODF
>
> **Option B: Full Sprint App Replica** (~2-3 days)  
> - Everything in Option A, PLUS
> - Full React/Next.js sprint management app
> - Team auth, AI features, real-time sync
> - Complete replacement for Lovable-built version
>
> **Recommendation**: Start with **Option A** to get immediate impact, then build Option B if needed.

---

## Proposed Changes (Option A: Website)

### Technology Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 15 with App Router
- **Styling**: Vanilla CSS with modern design tokens
- **Fonts**: Inter (primary), JetBrains Mono (accents)
- **Animations**: CSS animations + subtle JavaScript interactions
- **Deployment Ready**: Static export compatible

### Design Direction
Inspired by your reference sites:

| Reference | Key Elements to Adopt |
|-----------|----------------------|
| **Creators Corner** | Dark theme, purple/gradient accents, community-first messaging |
| **South Park Commons** | "-1 to 0" messaging, member stories, clean typography |
| **ODF** | Social proof (1000+ companies), intensity framing, outcome focus |
| **Y Combinator** | Orange accent, authority, direct CTAs |

### Site Structure

```
/
├── index.html          # Landing page
├── styles/
│   └── main.css        # Design system
└── script.js           # Interactions
```

---

### [NEW] Website Component Structure

#### Hero Section
- **Headline**: "Launch a Startup Skills System for AI Agents"
- **Subheadline**: Value prop from Habitat's mission
- **CTA**: "Get Started" / "Join Next Event"
- **Social proof**: "101+ founders launched prototypes"

#### Skills Showcase
- Interactive cards for each of the 11 skills
- Phase-by-phase breakdown with visual timeline
- Code snippets showing how to use with Claude Code

#### Why Habitat Section
- Three pillars (similar to joinhabitat.eu):
  - Testing beats planning
  - Community compounds  
  - Low stakes, high signal

#### Testimonials Carousel
- Real quotes from Habitat participants
- Company logos if available

#### Events/CTA Section
- Next event signup
- Perks (1:1 support, free credits, food included)

#### Footer
- Links to GitHub, LinkedIn, Luma events
- Made with 💙 in Leuven

---

## Verification Plan

### Browser Testing
1. **Open the website locally** using a simple HTTP server
2. **Verify responsive design** at mobile (375px), tablet (768px), and desktop (1200px+)
3. **Test all links** to GitHub, Luma events, etc.
4. **Verify animations** work smoothly
5. **Check accessibility** - keyboard navigation, color contrast

### Manual Verification (User)
- [ ] Review design matches inspiration sites' quality
- [ ] Verify copy resonates with Habitat positioning
- [ ] Test on real mobile device if possible

---

